The paper proposes an approach to sparse multinomial logistic regression using approximate message passing algorithms. This involves statistical modeling and optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and optimization subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses both synthetic and real-world datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
